<h1 style="margin-bottom:0px;">Install on AWS</h1><div class="f14 metric" style="color:#656668;display:flex;"><img src="/assets/images/calendar.png" style="height:12px;margin-top:auto;margin-bottom:auto;"><span class="updateDate">&nbsp; Updated on 26/06/2019</span> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <img src="/assets/images/updated.png" style="height:12px;margin-top:auto;margin-bottom:auto;"><span class="readTime">&nbsp; 1 minute to read</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><br><div class="mw-parser-output"><p>You can deploy the following containerized components of Operations Bridge Suite with Premium and Ultimate license editions on AWS.
</p>
<ul><li>Business Value Dashboard</li>
<li>COSO Data Lake</li>
<li>Performance Management</li>
<li>Digital Experience Monitoring</li>
<li>Collection Services</li></ul>
<p><br>
This document explains the installation and configuration of the Operations Bridge suite and you must perform the following steps in the given sequence:
</p>
<a class="buttonfullscr" onclick="javascript:loadingTableButton(this);"><button class="flscrbtn"><i class="material-icons flscricn">open_in_new</i><div style="margin: auto 5px;">View Fullscreen</div></button></a><table>
<tbody><tr>
<td><b>Phase</b>
</td>
<td><b>Objective</b>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>Plan
</td>
<td>Create  a deployment plan and the resources required for the installation of  the containerized components by performing the following steps:
<ol><li>Deployment modes</li>
<li>Support Matrix</li>
<li>Sizing recommendations</li>
<li>AWS region selection</li></ol>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>Prepare
</td>
<td>Using the systems created in the Plan phase, prepare  and configure the AWS resources required for the installation of containerized components by performing the  following steps:
<ol><li>Activate Docker Hub account</li>
<li>Prepare AWS resources
<ul><li>VPC</li>
<li>Subnets</li>
<li>NAT gateway</li>
<li>EC2 instances</li>
<li>Check connectivity</li>
<li>Target group</li>
<li>Network Load Balancer</li>
<li>Application Load Balancer</li>
<li>Amazon Route 53</li>
<li>Database (Amazon RDS)</li>
<li>Postgress RDS</li>
<li>Oracle RDS</li>
<li>Configure AWS EFS shares</li></ul></li>
<li>Configure EC2 instances</li>
<li>Configure EFS Storage</li>
<li>(optional) Configure an NFS Server</li>
<li>Download the installation Packages</li>
<li>Configure installation permission for a sudo user</li>
<li>Configure the install.properties file</li></ol>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>Deploy
</td>
<td>Install, deploy, and configure containerized components in your  environment by performing the following steps:
<ol><li>Install CDF</li>
<li>Select the deployment configuration</li>
<li>Download the container images</li>
<li>Deploy  and Configure Operations Bridge Suite</li>
<li>Reconfigure Ingress Controller</li>
<li>Verify the installation</li></ol>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
